RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 47. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ILIMITADA stalked the pace from four wide down the backstretch then moved up from three wide at the three furlong marker, tipping out to four wide in upper stretch for a late run at the leader and prevailed. BEAT THE DOUBLE went to an early pressured lead around to the first turn then took a clear lead while setting the pace through the final turn but was wore down the deep stretch but proved second best. CHARMING KAT tracked the leaders down the backstretch then moved between horses at the quarter pole, angled back inside to make a run on the inside into the stretch for a late rally. GRACE'S VISION raced in the middle of the pack down the backstretch then made an inside bid on the final turn but was outfinished in the stretch. SLIM CAUSEWAY was allowed to settled around the first turn then trailed the field to the final turn but made a strong inside run to finish strong. PENNIE'S MAGIC trailed the field early while saving ground down the backstretch, made a mild bid on the final turn but finished evenly. SENSE OF HEART pressed the pace from the two path around the first turn then settled off the pace to the three furlong marker and retreated. BLUERIDGEBALLERINA raced off the pace from off the rail to the three furlong marker and faded.
